buck naked or whatevs.

333
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:30,323
Hey, Xenovia, is it true
that Irina is leading

334
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:32,825
‐a cheer squad for us?
‐Totally.

335
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,661
I think she's set up a small
group over in the fan section

336
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:38,247
of the special
Grabbin' Dragon seating area.

337
00:16:38,289 --> 00:16:40,583
[NAUD]
Coming in from the East Gate,

338
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:44,045
may I present
the Sairaorg Bael team!

339
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:46,714
[CROWD cheering]

340
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:48,758
And coming in
from the West Gate,

341
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:52,428
may I present
the Rias Gremory team!

342
00:16:52,470 --> 00:16:54,430
Before we go out there,
I just want to thank

343
00:16:54,472 --> 00:16:56,390
each and everyone of you
for being a part

344
00:16:56,432 --> 00:16:58,392
of my precious family.

345
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:00,186
Is everyone ready?

346
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:02,313
Let's show them
what we're made of!

347
00:17:02,355 --> 00:17:03,814
[ALL]
Right!

348
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:10,196
[CROWD cheering]

349
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:30,925
[NAUD] How is everybody
doing this fine evening?

350
00:17:30,967 --> 00:17:33,886
I'm Naud Gamigin,
your emcee for tonight!

351
00:17:33,928 --> 00:17:35,680
I'd like to take a moment

352
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,723
to present the arbiter
for the game.

353
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:41,936
Give it up
for Rudiger Rosenkreutz!

354
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:44,021
We also have
a few special guests.

355
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:45,731
Welcome one
of our commentators,

356
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,191
you know him
as the Governor‐General

357
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,443
of the Fallen Angels.
It's Azazel!

358
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:52,029
‐[gasps]
‐Achtung, darlings!

359
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,698
We also have with us
the current champion

360
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:55,366
of the Rating Game. It's...

361
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:57,618
Diehauser Belial!

362
00:17:57,660 --> 00:17:59,078
[CROWD cheering]

363
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:01,372
Let's discuss the rules,
shall we?

364
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:04,250
Tonight we'll be utilizing
a popular variant item.

365
00:18:04,292 --> 00:18:06,002
Behold,
a Dice Figure Game!

366
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:09,630
At this time I'd like to invite
the Kings from each team

367
00:18:09,672 --> 00:18:12,675
to step up to the special
platform, please.

368
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:15,011
For those not familiar
with the dice game,

369
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:16,929
I will take this moment
to go over the rules

370
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:18,431
of how this will work.

371
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:22,184
For each round, the Kings
will use a normal six‐sided die.

372
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:24,729
Both Kings will then roll
their individual die

373
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:26,439
and the resulting total
of both numbers

374
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:28,524
will decide the members
of the match.

375
00:18:28,566 --> 00:18:31,902
For example, if the numbers
rolled are equal to eight,

376
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:33,487
each team may
send out members

377
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:35,781
that add up
to that specific number.

378
00:18:35,823 --> 00:18:37,617
The value
of each player depends

379
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:40,578
on what sort of evil piece
they consist of.

380
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:42,330
Pawns are one point,

381
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:44,248
knights and bishops
are three points,

382
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,833
rooks are five points,

383
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:47,585
and queens are equal
to nine points.

384
00:18:47,627 --> 00:18:50,546
Multiple players may
be chosen for the match,

385
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:52,173
so in the case
of eight points,

386
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:53,883
the King may send out
two knights to participate,

387
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:55,968
or it's also
considered acceptable

388
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:57,678
to mix and match
your evil pieces,

389
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,222
so you could also send out
a three‐point knight

390
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:02,016
and a five‐point rook to fight.

391
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:04,852
The number of evil pieces
used for a family member

392
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:06,979
is also taken into account
for calculating

393
00:19:07,021 --> 00:19:08,564
who to send into battle.

394
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:10,608
For instance,
Issei Hyodo is made up

395
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:12,985
of eight pawn pieces,
so he has a point value

396
00:19:13,027 --> 00:19:14,987
equal to the number eight.

397
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:16,822
But remember,
ladies and gentlemen,

398
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:19,158
you cannot send out
the same piece consecutively,

399
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,951
so choose carefully.
And of course,

400
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,412
let's not forget
about the Kings of each family.

401
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:25,956
Like normal, the game will end
if the King is defeated,

402
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:28,042
and so, after taking
all of the above factors

403
00:19:28,084 --> 00:19:30,544
into consideration,
the review board has decided

404
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:34,090
what the point value will be
for each the two Kings.

405
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:36,175
All right, my dears,
hold onto your hats,

406
00:19:36,217 --> 00:19:39,553
because we are about to
announce those numbers!

407
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:42,807
Sairaorg Bael
will be worth 12 points!

408
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:45,601
Rias Gremory
will be worth eight points!

409
00:19:45,643 --> 00:19:49,146
Now, now, Lord Sairaorg may
have a higher point value,

410
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:51,524
but that also means
he cannot participate in a match

411
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:53,317
without a maximum
roll of 12,

412
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:55,778
so that could work
to Rias Gremory's advantage!

413
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:58,614
The last rule is regarding
Phoenix Tears!

414
00:19:58,656 --> 00:20:01,242
Thanks to the Phoenix family,
each team will have

415
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:04,537
one vial available to use
at any time during the game.

416
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,622
Great, meaning we have
to prepare for the possibility

417
00:20:06,664 --> 00:20:09,834
of defeating Sairaorg
not once, but twice.

418
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,419
Balls.

419
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:14,046
[NAUD]
Enough, my blood‐thirsty rubes!

420
00:20:14,088 --> 00:20:17,591
‐Let's get started!
‐The match begins now.

421
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:21,429
Lord Sairaorg Bael
and Princess Rias Gremory,

422
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:23,806
let's get ready to rumble!

423
00:20:23,848 --> 00:20:25,599
[cheering]

424
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,773
[RUDIGER] It's time
to decide the first match.

425
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:34,859
Kings, please pick up your die!

426
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,822
Let's roll!

427
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,453
[NAUD]
Sairaorg Bael has rolled a one!

428
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:47,747
Rias Gremory has rolled a two!

429
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,290
The total is three.

430
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,834
Since the value of the pawns
on each side is too high,

431
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,836
only a bishop or a knight
may be chosen

432
00:20:53,878 --> 00:20:55,838
to participate
in the first round.

433
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:58,382
Now the question is whom
will each family choose

434
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:00,551
to send out
for this opening match?

435
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:02,803
[RUDIGER]
You have five minutes to plan.

436
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:05,473
Please choose your champion
within that time frame.

437
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:11,604
[IRINA] This is it. I wonder
who they'll choose to go first?

438
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:14,607
[RUDIGER] The five‐minute
time limit is nearly up.

439
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:20,029
Kiba! It's all up to you,
so go kick some "A."

440
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:24,200
I'm planning on it.

441
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,869
‐[chuckles]
‐[humphs]

442
00:21:36,337 --> 00:21:38,380
[NAUD] It looks like
the participants from each team

443
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:41,467
are now entering
the designated battle field.

444
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:45,054
The Gremory family has chosen
the Noble of God‐like Speed,

445
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:50,059
the Knight of Princess Rias.
Give it up for Kiba Yuto!

446
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,852
[CROWD cheering]

447
00:22:07,368 --> 00:22:09,620
Finally, the game's
about to begin.

448
00:22:09,662 --> 00:22:11,997
♪

449
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:55,851
[ISSEI] "As a family member
